    intro_text: 'The cream suit is summer tailoring at its most effortlessly elegant — a cloth that reflects light, conveys ease, and carries a quiet confidence that no other colour quite matches. Rooted in British summer dressing, from Henley Regatta to garden parties in the Home Counties, the cream suit demands an understanding of proportion and restraint. Worn correctly, it is one of the most striking things a man can put on. At William Ashford, our cream suits are cut in fine linen and lightweight wools to perform beautifully in the warmer months.',
