    intro_text: 'The herringbone suit is British tailoring at its most textural — a cloth whose distinctive V-shaped weave adds depth and character that plain wools simply cannot replicate. Worn in charcoal, mid-grey, or navy, a herringbone suit reads as authoritative and refined; in brown or tobacco tones, it carries the warmth of a country estate whilst remaining perfectly at home in the city. At William Ashford, herringbone cloth is a perennial favourite, favoured for the way it catches light and rewards close inspection.',
