    intro_text: 'The monk strap shoe occupies a fascinating place in British menswear — more decorative than an Oxford, more formal than a loafer, and more characterful than almost anything else in a well-dressed man\'s shoe wardrobe. The single monk strap, with its clean buckled strap, communicates understated distinction; the double monk strap, with its two parallel buckles, makes a bolder statement that rewards confidence. At William Ashford, we consider the monk strap one of the most interesting and rewarding choices a man can make in footwear.',
