    intro_text: 'The roll-neck worn beneath a suit jacket is one of modern menswear\'s most compelling propositions — a combination that blends the authority of tailoring with the ease of knitwear, and that carries the spirit of 1960s British cool into the present with complete confidence. It is a pairing that requires care: the wrong roll-neck, in the wrong fabric, with the wrong suit, creates a confused rather than considered impression. Done correctly, however, the roll-neck suit is an effortlessly sophisticated alternative to the shirt-and-tie combination, and one that is increasingly seen in the most stylish company.',
    style_tips: `Choose a fine-gauge roll-neck in merino wool, cashmere, or silk — thick, chunky knits are too bulky beneath a suit jacket and create awkward bulk at the shoulders.\nMidnight navy, charcoal grey, and black roll-necks are the most versatile under suit jackets — they provide contrast without disrupting the clean line of the jacket lapel.\nA roll-neck worn with a suit requires no additional accessories at the neck — the high collar is itself the statement; pocket squares and tie pins are superfluous.\nFor the most sophisticated look, choose a roll-neck that is one or two tones darker than your suit — a charcoal roll-neck with a mid-grey suit creates depth and harmony.\nAn ivory or cream roll-neck worn beneath a navy or charcoal suit creates a striking, clean contrast that reads as both modern and refined.\nKeep the roll-neck smooth and lint-free — under jacket lighting, pilling and fluff are highly visible; use a fabric shaver regularly to maintain a pristine surface.`,
